    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 5000, 9300 AND 9400 SERIES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsection id="s11008r" division="truck" formnum="CTS-5063R" date="03/01/1996">
        <title>CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 5000, 9300 AND 9400 SERIES</title>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>5000</truckmodel>
            </configure>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9300
                    <daterange>
                        <enddate>12/31/1992</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
                <truckmodel>9400
                    <daterange>
                        <enddate>12/31/1992</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The clutch control linkage (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1100801">Figure 1</hotlnk>) consists of a suspended clutch pedal connected by a rod
                    to a relay (bellcrank) which is, in turn, connected by another rod to the clutch release shaft
                    lever.
                </para>
                <para>The clutch pedal and relay shafts pivot on low friction bushings of non-metallic (Acetal)
                    material.
                </para>
                <para>Adjustments are provided to establish correct initial settings and to compensate for wear of
                    clutch disc facings.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1100801" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1100801" filename="../figg11/g1100801.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Clutch Control Linkage (Typical)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. RELEASE SHAFT LEVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. CONTROL ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. PEDAL SHAFT LEVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. BEARING</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. DASH PANEL (ENGINE TUNNEL)</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. PEDAL SHAFT</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. STEERING COLUMN SUPPORT BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. CLUTCH PEDAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
